This paper is about a convolutional neural network for multi-modal image segmentation, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of dense connections, which is a technique in deep learning (cs.LG) and the network architecture is designed to learn complex combinations between modalities, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper reports on experiments and evaluations, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
